1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,199
Hey everybody.

2
00:00:01,199 --> 00:00:05,539
Welcome to this a one English listening practice video.

3
00:00:05,580 --> 00:00:11,139
You can use this video to practice your listening and comprehension as I speak.

4
00:00:11,180 --> 00:00:17,894
Before we start, remember to subscribe to the channel, click on the bell, and follow us on Instagram.

5
00:00:17,935 --> 00:00:18,994
You ready?

6
00:00:18,994 --> 00:00:23,154
So today, I'm gonna talk about the supermarket.

7
00:00:23,154 --> 00:00:28,935
This is a useful topic because most people buy food from supermarkets.

8
00:00:29,540 --> 00:00:37,820
One important note, in The US, many people use the phrase grocery store instead of supermarket.

9
00:00:38,019 --> 00:00:42,140
I usually say grocery store, but you can use both.

10
00:00:42,725 --> 00:00:46,845
So first, let's talk about big supermarkets.

11
00:00:47,045 --> 00:00:50,605
The most famous supermarket is Walmart.

12
00:00:50,645 --> 00:00:54,605
Walmart is really big and sells many items.

13
00:00:55,160 --> 00:01:01,920
They sell food, clothes, electronics, furniture, and much more.

14
00:01:02,199 --> 00:01:04,160
Walmart has everything.

15
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:08,160
In big supermarkets, there are a lot of cheap items.

16
00:01:08,755 --> 00:01:12,554
Personally, I don't like big supermarkets.

17
00:01:12,755 --> 00:01:18,794
I prefer smaller supermarkets because they often have better products.

18
00:01:18,995 --> 00:01:25,569
I like to buy organic food, so I search for small organic stores.

19
00:01:25,930 --> 00:01:31,089
These stores are usually more expensive than big supermarkets.

20
00:01:31,210 --> 00:01:39,145
Organic food is more expensive than non organic food, but I think it's worth the price.

21
00:01:39,345 --> 00:01:44,265
In big supermarkets, I can't find the products I like.

22
00:01:44,465 --> 00:01:48,105
That's why I go to small local stores.

23
00:01:48,225 --> 00:01:52,309
There are also some very small supermarkets too.

24
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:55,509
We call these convenience stores.

25
00:01:55,630 --> 00:01:59,910
For example, seven Eleven is a convenience store.

26
00:02:00,030 --> 00:02:05,990
These stores sell some food and drinks, but they don't have a lot of items.

27
00:02:06,565 --> 00:02:11,065
I go to convenience stores when I need to buy just one

28
00:02:11,065 --> 00:02:16,685
or two items, but I don't usually shop at convenience stores.

29
00:02:16,885 --> 00:02:20,045
They don't have all the items that I need.

30
00:02:20,085 --> 00:02:21,005
How about you?

31
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:27,420
Do you prefer big supermarkets, small supermarkets, or convenience stores?

32
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:30,700
Some people don't go to supermarkets.

33
00:02:30,820 --> 00:02:33,100
They buy their groceries online.

34
00:02:33,555 --> 00:02:37,195
Nowadays, you can buy everything online.

35
00:02:37,315 --> 00:02:41,035
You order it and someone brings it to your house.

36
00:02:41,315 --> 00:02:43,995
This is becoming a popular option.

37
00:02:44,275 --> 00:02:49,760
I order some items online, but I don't order food online.

38
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:50,620
Okay.

39
00:02:50,620 --> 00:02:54,960
Now, let's learn some important supermarket vocabulary.

40
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:58,480
Our first vocabulary word is cart.

41
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:02,320
When you enter a grocery store, you grab a cart.

42
00:03:02,655 --> 00:03:07,335
You put all of your items in your cart while you're shopping.

43
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:13,895
Or if you're only buying a few items, you can use a basket, which you carry.

44
00:03:13,935 --> 00:03:16,295
Our next word is aisle.

45
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:20,550
Aisles are the rows of products in a store.

46
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:24,950
You walk up and down the aisles when you go shopping.

47
00:03:25,070 --> 00:03:28,230
The next phrase is on sale.

48
00:03:28,270 --> 00:03:34,695
When an item is on sale, this means that it has a lower price than normal.

49
00:03:34,815 --> 00:03:37,655
I love when items are on sale.

50
00:03:37,775 --> 00:03:38,515
Okay.

51
00:03:38,515 --> 00:03:39,735
One more word.

52
00:03:39,935 --> 00:03:41,015
Cashier.

53
00:03:41,135 --> 00:03:45,655
The cashier is the person that you pay when you're done shopping.

54
00:03:45,990 --> 00:03:50,030
In The US, cashiers are usually friendly.

55
00:03:50,229 --> 00:03:55,870
Nowadays, in some supermarkets, you can pay without a cashier.

56
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:58,190
This is called self checkout.

57
00:03:58,715 --> 00:04:05,235
Some people prefer cashiers and other people prefer the self checkout option.

58
00:04:05,355 --> 00:04:07,235
I like both options.

59
00:04:07,355 --> 00:04:09,555
Alright, that's all for today.

60
00:04:09,514 --> 00:04:12,915
Leave a comment and tell me where you buy your food.

61
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:15,940
And remember to subscribe to the channel,

62
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:21,760
click on the bell, and follow us on Instagram for more English tips and lessons.

63
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:23,040
I'll see you next time.
